      <div type="eventFactoids">
        <listEvent>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-1" ana="#governance">
            <!-- We are going to call this sample prosopography document, file 633, so the xml id indicates that this is eventFactoid number one for document 633 -->
            <!-- Multiple analysis refs encouraged and allowed. -->
            <desc> King's began to rule in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78"
                >Edessa</placeName> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="-0132" calendar="Gregorian">132 B.C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="180" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 180</date></orig>
              </choice>.
              <!-- See this for our policies on Dates http://syriaca.org/documentation/dates.html and in https://docs.google.com/document/d/175Yx1uf_HaXRA6O36p83vf-ECFWLGFNbUXoDF7ffVDs/edit#-->
            </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl> <!-- ALL BIBLs SHOULD HAVE type="source" ADDED TO THEM! -->
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 1</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-2" ana="#accession">
            <desc>
              <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Augustus">Augustus</persName> became emperor
              in <choice>
                <corr><date when="-0044" calendar="Gregorian">44 B.C.E.</date></corr>
                <sic><date when="-0045" calendar="Gregorian">45 B.C.E.</date></sic>
                <orig><date when-custom="266" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 266</date></orig>
              </choice>.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 2</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-3" ana="#architecture #governance">
            <desc>
              <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVI">Abgar</persName> builds a <ref
                target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/architecture">mausoleum</ref> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0088" calendar="Gregorian">88 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="0400" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 400</date></orig>
              </choice>.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 4</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-4" ana="#apostasy">
            <desc>
              <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Marcion">Marcion</persName> forsook the
                <orgName>catholic church</orgName> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0138" calendar="Gregorian">138 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="0449" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 449</date></orig>
              </choice>
            </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 5</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-5" ana="#war #violence">
            <desc>
              <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/LuciusVerus">Lucius Verus</persName> and
                <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Commodus">his brother Commodus</persName>
              conquered <orgName type="state">the Parthians</orgName> in <date when="0166">the fifth
                year of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/LuciusVerus"
                >Lucius'</persName>reign</date>. </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 7</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-6" ana="#naturalDisaster">
            <desc>
              <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/191">The Daisan river</placeName> flooded
                <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0201-11" calendar="Gregorian">201 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="513-2" datingMethod="Seleucid-SyriacMonths">A. Gr. 513, in
                    the month Tishrin the latter</date></orig>
              </choice> during the reign of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVIII"
                >Abgar VIII</persName>.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 1</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-7" ana="#decree">
            <desc>In <choice>
                <reg><date when="0201" calendar="Gregorian">201 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="513" calendar="Seleucid">A. Gr. 513</date></orig>
              </choice>, <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVIII">Abgar VIII</persName>
              commanded that <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Anonymi6"> those who live in
                the portico in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78"
                >Edessa.</placeName></persName> leave their houses in the winter.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 2</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-8" ana="#architecture #decree">
            <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVIII">Abgar VIII</persName>
              commanded to be built <placeName
                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/Winter-royal-residence@Tabara">a royal winter house at
                Tabara</placeName> and he dwelt there during the winters.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 2-3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-9" ana="#architecture">
            <desc>A palace was build for <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVIII">Abgar
                VIII</persName> in <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78"
              >Edessa.</placeName>.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-10" ana="#architecture">
            <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Anonymi8"> The nobles of <persName
                  ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVIII">Abgar VIII</persName></persName> built
              homes near the king.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-11" ana="#decree">
            <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVIII">Abgar VIII</persName> remitted
              the taxes of Edessa and the surrounding towns after the flood of <choice>
                <reg><date when="0201" calendar="Gregorian">201 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="513" calendar="Seleucid">A. Gr. 513</date></orig>
              </choice>.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-12" ana="#writing">
            <desc>
              <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Yahab"><roleName>Mar</roleName>
                <forename>Yahab</forename>
                <addName>Bar Shemesh</addName></persName> and <persName
                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Kaiuma"><forename>Kaiuma</forename>
                <addName>Bar Magartat</addName></persName> recorded the flooding of <placeName
                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0201" calendar="Gregorian">201 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="513" calendar="Seleucid">A. Gr. 513</date></orig>
              </choice>. </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-13" ana="#writing">
            <desc>
              <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/BarDin">Bar Din</persName> and <persName
                ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Bulid">Bulid</persName> archived the record of the
              flooding of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0201" calendar="Gregorian">201 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="513" calendar="Seleucid">A. Gr. 513</date></orig>
              </choice>. </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 8</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-14" ana="#architecture">
            <desc>
              <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/AbgarVIII">Abgar VIII</persName> builds a
                <ref target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/architecture">palace</ref> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0205" calendar="Gregorian">205 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="517" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 517</date></orig>
              </choice> in <!-- the text reads "in his city/town". I think this is Edessa? -->. </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 9</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-15" ana="#naturalDisaster">
            <desc>The walls of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName> are
              destroyed in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0302" calendar="Gregorian">302 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="0614" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 614</date></orig>
              </choice>.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 3-4</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 11</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-16" ana="#architecture #sacredSites">
            <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Conon">Conon</persName> laid the
              foundations of the <ref target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/architecture">Church</ref>
              of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0312" calendar="Gregorian">312 C.E.</date></reg>
                <orig><date when-custom="624" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 624</date></orig>
              </choice>. </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 4</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 12</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-17" ana="#sacredSites #architecture">
            <desc><name ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Shaʿad">Shaʿad</name> finished building the
                <ref target="http://syriaca.org/keyword/architecture">Church</ref> of <placeName
                ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>.</desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 4</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 12</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-18" ana="#architecture">
            <desc>The cemetary of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName>
              was built in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0324" calendar="Gregorian">324 C.E.</date></reg>
                <!-- Here is a good example of why we need clear standards. We don't know if 635 is 323 or 324. So, we could encode this date as not before 323 and not after 324. However, the text reads that this event took place the year before Nicaea so clearly we should chose 324. But that process will not always be so clear. If we will not always go with not before and not after, we ought to be clear about how and why we make that call.. -->
                <orig><date when-custom="635" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 635</date></orig>
              </choice></desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 4</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 13</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
          <event xml:id="eventFactoid633-19" ana="#accession">
            <desc><persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/Aitallaha">Aitallaha</persName> became
              bishop of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/78">Edessa</placeName> in <choice>
                <reg><date when="0325" calendar="Gregorian">325 C.E.</date></reg>
                <!-- Fix these dates! -->
                <orig><date when-custom="636" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 636</date></orig>
              </choice>.
              <!-- This raises a number of problems. The English translation has ammended the text without comment. In mss. section 13 refers to the year 635 A. Gr. while section 14 refers to 636 A. Gr. But, they refer to the same events. Moreover, section 15 of the Chronicle that in the next year, 325 C. E., the council of Nicaea took place. While there is no comment in the English footnotes, Hallier discusses the issues at some length. And I thought collecting factoids would make things easier! How will we discuss these kinds of problems?-->
            </desc>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="pp"><ptr target="#bib663-1"/>pp 4</biblScope></bibl>
            <bibl type="source"><biblScope type="part"><ptr
                    target="#bib663-2"/>Section 14</biblScope></bibl>
          </event>
        </listEvent>
      </div>
